schedule data type properties

The following table describes the properties included in the schedule data type. Property name

Data type

Description

Notes

local

local

Specifies the schedule for the replication link on the local system.

This property is not valid on a POST request for an inbound active/passive link.

remote

remote

Specifies the schedule for the replication link on the remote system.

This property is not valid on a POST request for an outbound active/passive link. Example

Here’s an XML example of the schedule data type:

<schedule> <local> <scheduleOverride>NONE</scheduleOverride> <transition> <time>Sun:00</time> <performanceLevel>HIGH</performanceLevel>

</transition> <transition> <time>Sun:06</time> <performanceLevel>MEDIUM</performanceLevel> </transition> <transition> <time>Sat:00</time> <performanceLevel>HIGH</performanceLevel> </transition> <transition> <time>Sat:06</time> <performanceLevel>MEDIUM</performanceLevel> </transition> </local> <remote> <scheduleOverride>NONE</scheduleOverride> <transition> <time>Sun:00</time> <performanceLevel>HIGH</performanceLevel> </transition> <transition> <time>Mon:00</time> <performanceLevel>MEDIUM</performanceLevel> </transition> </remote> </schedule>

